    "body": "### Feature already in Vim?\n\nn/a\n\n### Feature description\n\nI would like to be able to highlight a particular region in a particular buffer, but only in one window. It seems that this is maybe possible using :ownsyntax, and then defining a new syntax for that window, but this seems incredibly complicated compared the wonderful neovim extmarks, which let me just specify the bounds of the region and the highlight group.\r\n\r\nUnfortunately, there does not seem to be any way of scoping visual aspects of an extmark (highlight, virtual text) to a particular window - everything about an extmark displays in all windows.\r\n\r\nIt would not be quite enough for my use case, but even :winhighlight seems to not work with extmarks. E.g.,\r\n\r\n`:lua vim.api.nvim_buf_set_extmark(0, vim.api.nvim_create_namespace('test'), 0, 1, {hl_group=\"Visual\", end_row=0, end_col=2})`\r\n\r\n`:set winhighlight=Visual:IncSearch`\r\n\r\nThis correctly makes actual visual mode look different in the current window, but does not affect the appearance of the extmark with visual group highlighting.\r\n",
    "closed_at": "2024-02-21T18:21:15Z",
